## Mixed Syntax Compatibility

You can mix new and legacy syntax seamlessly:

@username: [text required]
@password: [password required]

### New syntax (recommended)
@[submit "Sign In"]

### Legacy syntax (still supported)
@forgot_password: [button label="Forgot Password?" onclick="forgotPassword()"]

---

## Benefits Demonstrated

### üéØ **Semantic Clarity**
- **Input Fields**: `@field: [type]` for data collection
- **Actions**: `@[action "label"]` for user actions

### üìù **Markdown Compatibility**
- Avoids confusion with Markdown links `[text](url)`
- Clear FormDown namespace with `@[...]`

### ‚ö° **Concise Syntax**
Compare the old vs new approach:

**Before:**
```formdown
@submit_button: [submit label="Send Message" class="btn-primary"]
```

**After:**
```formdown
@[submit "Send Message" class="btn-primary"]
```

### üîÑ **Full Backward Compatibility**
Both syntaxes work together perfectly:

@email: [email required]
@[submit "Subscribe"]
@cancel_btn: [button label="Cancel" onclick="cancel()"]

### üé® **Framework Ready**
Works with any CSS framework:

